Dave have you tried calling local craftsmen who work w/ sandblasting
equipement on a regular basis? Like a gravestone maker or the like? just
a thought. 
Ask around until you think you've got a good answer. One of the local
sandblasters I know here used to work with no mask or the wrong mask and
gave himself some sort of poisioning. Now can hardly do anything b/c of
weakness and such. I too would start with the gravestone makers. They do
my sandblasting on hearty metal (thick stuff). Wouldn't let them loose
on a door or anything. 
Chris Mills in TN
